en_806874_0	Minister Thalatha Athukorale has said that the judiciary was acting independently sans any political interference.
en_806874_1	The Minister made this reference joining in a function held at the Elapaatha Divisional Secretariat Division in Ratnapura.
en_806874_2	It was organized to hand over 1205 Samurdhi entitlements under the programme of giving Samurdhi entitlements to 600 thousand families.
en_806874_3	A group including many public representatives was present.
en_806874_4	Minister Thalatha Athukorale said that they had frequently referred to the situation that prevailed in the judiciary in the past.
en_806874_5	Now the situation has improved.
en_806874_6	Chief Justices were sent home in the past.
en_806874_7	The judiciary is now independent.
en_806874_8	It is the same for everyone.
en_806874_9	No political influence is necessary.
en_806874_10	Those who want to maintain poverty in the country are those who want to interfere in the judiciary.
en_806874_11	She said that the public servants have been given the freedom.
en_806874_12	Even the police have been given the freedom to engage in their duties.
